# Create tools listing endpoint



## Requirements

- [ ] Create `GET /api/v1/tools` endpoint returning available tools
- [ ] List all registered tools with basic metadata (id, name, description)
- [ ] Support pagination with `limit` and `offset` query parameters
- [ ] Support filtering by `category` and `enabled` status
- [ ] Return JSON response with tool objects and pagination metadata
- [ ] Implement proper error handling for invalid query parameters

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Endpoint returns 200 with paginated tool list
- [ ] Response includes at least: id, name, description, category, enabled, created_at
- [ ] Default pagination limit is 20, max is 100
- [ ] Filter by category works (e.g., `?category=file-system`)
- [ ] Filter by enabled status works (e.g., `?enabled=true`)
- [ ] Invalid query parameters return 400 with descriptive error
- [ ] Endpoint is authenticated and rate-limited
- [ ] Tests cover all filters and pagination edge cases


